The paper deals with the study of straight-line drawings and their properties, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of ply number and its relaxation, vertex-ply, involves the analysis of graphs and their structures, which can be categorized under data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the relationship between ply and proximity drawings, which can be classified under graph theory (cs.GT) and computational topology (cs.SI).
